 it — I’ll give you simple, exam-ready commands from scratch so you can confidently do push, clone, and pull 👍

🔹 1. INITIAL SETUP (only once)
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"
🔹 2. CREATE + PUSH PROJECT (Local → GitHub)
Step 1: Go to your project folder
cd your-folder-name
Step 2: Initialize git
git init
Step 3: Add files
git add .
Step 4: Commit
git commit -m "First commit"
Step 5: Connect to GitHub repo

(After creating repo on GitHub)

git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repository-name.git
Step 6: Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
🔹 3. CLONE REPOSITORY (GitHub → Local)
git clone https://github.com/username/repository-name.git

Then go inside:

cd repository-name
🔹 4. PULL LATEST CHANGES
git pull origin main
🔹 5. PUSH CHANGES AGAIN (after editing files)
git add .
git commit -m "Updated files"
git push origin main
🔹 QUICK MEMORY TRICK (VERY IMPORTANT FOR EXAM)

👉 Push = Local → GitHub
👉 Pull = GitHub → Local
👉 Clone = Copy repo to your system

🔹 COMMON ERRORS (just in case)
❌ Permission error

Use:

git config --global credential.helper store
❌ Repo already exists

Skip git init

🔹 SUPER SHORT VERSION (for writing in exam)
git init
git add .
git commit -m "msg"
git remote add origin <repo-url>
git push -u origin main

git clone <repo-url>

git pull origin main
